22/02/2008
TIRANA, Albania -- Ilir Meta, the leader of the Socialist Movement for Integration (SMI), announced on Thursday (February 21st) that SMI leaders decided to abandon the opposition left-wing coalition and create a new initiative called "Left for Integration", to represent the progressive left. Meta cited growing disagreements with the largest opposition party, the Socialist Party, especially over electoral reform. (Panorama, Shekulli, Kohajone - 22/02/08; Balkanweb, Top-Channel, Makfax 21/02/08)
